Why yes, Clarissa – comment away!

 <https://profile.theguardian.com/user/id/2412395> clarissaoakes  
<https://profile.theguardian.com/user/id/2412395> 06 January 2017 1:55pm 
<https://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/90644585> 
Is this a place to comment on Rafael Behr's piece? I have to say I'm getting 
tired of comment pieces that remark on how pathetic the government is in its 
response to the referendum result and its approach to grasping what leaving the 
EU means. We cannot keep waiting on this government to show the way. The 
Guardian needs to take a stronger line in pointing out that the constitution of 
the UK has changed through our being a member of the EU and that leaving the EU 
means drawing up a new constitutional settlement. This is not a task for one 
political party to take forward, especially one that draws its support from a 
minority of voters and from England primarily.
