 <https://profile.theguardian.com/user/id/4362689> Badmoodme  
<https://profile.theguardian.com/user/id/4362689> 06 January 2017 3:08pm 
<https://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/90649887> 
"While I agree with those who were critical of his failure to curb the 
surveillance state and drones, I still believe that in time he will be regarded 
as one of America’s better presidents."

Surveillance state and use of drones in warfare isn't limited to Obama and any 
